six-month net income surged 40 percent from a year earlier as
loans and deposits grew.  Profit rose to 17.9 billion shillings ($7.2 million) from
12.8 billion shillings a year earlier, the Kampala-based  Bank of
Baroda Uganda Ltd. (BOBU)  said in an advertisement published today in
New Vision newspaper.  Loans increased 30 percent to 293.2 billion shillings, and
deposits climbed 13 percent to 435.3 billion shillings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
